      "U07PYD02V2S"
    ],
    "is_locked": false,
    "subscribed": false,
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "obKYk",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "I was looking at Christopher Alexander's "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "The Timeless Way of Building",
                "style": {
                  "italic": true
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " — and, while I could spend some time with it and figure out how his ideas apply to software, I thought someone has probably already done that. Does anyone have links they'd recommend?\n\n(Not sure what I'm specifically looking for, though 1) ways to express the differences between good and bad design on a team and 2) examples of software \"pattern languages\" that are at a similarly high-level as his architecture language sound particularly interesting.)"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
